			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>Job Summary:</strong><br />
	Market products by managing staff; maintaining response operations; maintaining quality ratings.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Duties and Responsibilities:</strong><br />
	&bull; Maintains marketing staff by orienting and training employees; maintaining a safe and secure work environment; developing personal growth opportunities.<br />
	&bull; Accomplishes staff results by communicating job expectations; planning, monitoring, and appraising job results; coaching, counseling, and disciplining employees; initiating, coordinating, and enforcing systems, policies, and procedures.<br />
	&bull; Maintains customer response operations by establishing work schedules; assigning employees; providing back-up.<br />
	&bull; Maintains quality service by establishing and enforcing standards; training representatives; monitoring calls; surveying customers; evaluating outcomes.<br />
	&bull; Resolves customer problems by providing telemarketing service; maintaining reference manuals and dialogue guides; providing information; answering questions.<br />
	&bull; Maintains work process flows by coordinating information and requirements with related operational departments; participating with and providing resources to business improvement teams.<br />
	&bull; Keeps management informed by preparing reports; making presentations; interpreting information; making recommendations.<br />
	&bull; Maintains professional and technical knowledge by attending educational workshops; reviewing professional publications; establishing personal networks; benchmarking state-of-the-art practices; participating in professional societies.<br />
	&bull; Contributes to team effort by accomplishing related results as needed.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Skills/Qualifications:</strong></p>
<p>
	&bull; At least a Bachelor&rsquo;s/College Degree in Management, Marketing, PR, Mass Communication or equivalent.<br />
	&bull; Minimum five (5) years of working experience in related field is required, three (3) years of which is in supervisory or managerial level.<br />
	&bull; Essential Skills: Supervision, Market Knowledge, Subordinate Involvement, Planning, Quality Focus, Resolving Conflict, Customer Service, Managing Processes, Presentation Skills, Technical Understanding, Financial Planning and Strategy</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
